A course with the biggest high and lows... Lectures are completely unintelligible, but prof's really funny and engaging.  Don't bother taking notes, just READ, and know the materials!! No slides uploaded. Class content extremely interesting and prof is undoubtedly knowledgeable and passionate, but unfortunately all of that doesn't make up for the fact that  lectures and test/essay questions are extremely unclear. In class, I often would have no idea what he's trying to say, and on tests/essays you either hit or miss completely.

Really nice guy and very generous with marks. However, the course itself was super unorganized, and I basically had no clue how his lectures related to what the course description said the course would be about.
He's a super cool guy. I personally just didn't handle his free style lecturing well. He doesn't have notes or slides or anything like that. Overall though, he's great at what he does.
